This paper deals with multi-objective reinforcement learning (MORL) algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the concept of Pareto optimality, which is relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
